pr_review_comment_body:
@menduo The other classes are called `CloudFlareDns` `AcmeDnsDns` 
so I think this should also be called `HeDns` so that we can have consistency. 

We should probably rename `AliyunDNS` to `AliyunDns` for the same reasons; but I do not know if that will break compatibility for you. If it would break compatibility, maybe we can do it in another Pull request rather than this one

Nope not quiet it doesn't set

last_stride_y = stride_y;
last_stride_x = stride_x;
last_padding_y = padding_y;
last_padding_x = padding_x;

 that's the only "setup" the CPU implementation seems to do.

You could call this one in the other one to make it nicer and reduce code duplication yes. 
I thought about that but left it out for now.

The reason why is there is a much larger difference in the CUDA version but I have to keep the same signatures as interface between the two have to stay the same

You could merge this with the `elif` above it:
```python
    elif isinstance(obj, list) or isinstance(obj, ImmutableList):
        return '[{}]'.format(seq(obj, **kwargs))
```

Instead of removing `**kwargs`, can we fix the invocation to properly pass `**kwargs`?

```
def _lint_file(self, *args, **kwargs):
    return restructuredtext_lint.lint(*args, **kwargs)
```

From [style guide](https://github.com/numenta/nupic/wiki/Python-Style-Guide#quotes); 

> By default, double quotes should be used for all strings.

Here and elsewhere throughout the file.

Code like this:

```js
// Source: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Fetch_API/Using_Fetch
fetch(url, {
  method: 'POST', // or 'PUT'
  body: JSON.stringify(data), // data can be `string` or {object}!
  headers: new Headers({
    'Content-Type': 'application/json'
  })
}).then(res => res.json())
.catch(error => console.error('Error:', error))
.then(response => console.log('Success:', response));
```

terrifies me. I would prefer to see less code like that.

I think we need to set `mParentRequestState` to `kParentIdle` so that next time `BecomeChild()` is called it does not return `BUSY`. Here is what we changed (expanding the `else if`)...
```                     
                             BecomeDetached();
                    }
                    else
                    {
                        mParentRequestState = kParentIdle;
                        
                        // return to sleepy operation
                        if ((mDeviceMode & ModeTlv::kModeRxOnWhenIdle) == 0)
                        {
                            netif.GetMeshForwarder().GetDataPollManager().SetAttachMode(false);
                            netif.GetMeshForwarder().SetRxOnWhenIdle(false);
                        }
                    }
```

I mean that it is better to do

```
@mock.patch('os.path.isdir')
@mock.patch('os.path.listdir')
@mock.patch('requests....')
```

instead of mocking the same code that you're testing -- these utility methods are untested if you're mocking them.

